EMG¶

.txt¶

In [15]:
import os
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
fs = 1000
dir = os.path.join(os.path.realpath(''),'Data/EMG/emg3.txt')
emg_raw = []
with open(dir) as f:
    lines = f.readlines()
for l in lines:
    emg_raw.append(float(l.replace("\n","")))
time = np.linspace(0, len(emg_raw) / fs, len(emg_raw))
# plot EMG signal
fig = plt.figure()
plt.plot(time, emg_raw)
plt.xlabel('Time (sec)')
plt.ylabel('EMG (mV)')
fig_name = 'rawEMG.png'
fig.set_size_inches(w=11,h=7)
fig.savefig(fig_name)
